Ghana Trip 18-22 October Experience announcement We are super excited to announce the Chillers Getaway, an exciting all expenses paid experience to Ghana. Three of you and your plus ones will join me (MacG) and the whole crew for our first visit to Ghana. How it works. To win this once in a lifetime experience with us. Visit www.epic-contests.com and find the Chiller's Getaway on the platform. Enter by submitting a piece of content (photo/video) of yourself. Then you have to earn the highest number of credits by either taking the quiz, using promo codes from our social media platforms or by purchasing credits. There is a live leaderboard on the platform that shows you in real time, who is leading the contest. When the countdown clock hits zero, the top three participants with the highest number of credits will win the experience. Other rules Contest entries close on the 29 September 2021 and the contest ends on the 30 September. We travel on the 18-22 October 2021. Africa’s biggest premium beer brand, Castle Lite is proud to announce that not only is Castle Lite Unlocks In Bed With returning for a second episode this week, the show has now been commissioned to stream live to you every week until the end of the lockdown period in Mzansi.



The king himself, Stogie T will bring the show to sub-zero temperatures as he shows off his rap prowess that comes with a 15-year strong repertoire of skill, effortless cool and unmatched lyricism all from the comfort of his home.

What are the dos and donts of braais since we are going to be doing a lot of those but keeping it to under a 100 people. item.content:encoded: New week means another episode of your favourite podcast. The Mabenas are home alone this week as the Ghost Lady is feeling a little bit under the weather but show must go on. This week we look at some of the suggestion emails sent through by you the chillers on how to make your fav even better than it already is. What is ASMR - we look it the soothing sounds it makes and if it can make you fall asleep. A Reece, is he the best we have in the country and can we name him the SA Jay Z, the gloves are off the gents have a say on the matter plus Patrice Motsepe goes big with banking and yes Thabang is in the house once again. Another fire Podcast and Chill with MacG episode.

item.content:encoded: Another episode of Podcast and Chill is here and more relevant than most music awards ceremonies. Speaking of which, are they still a thing? The team break down the interest people have in award ceremonies. Mabena has Premium now and he hints at watching The River has people shedding a tears. We celebrate the life of Kobe Bryant after news of his tragic passing plus Kabza and Maphorisa manage to sneak in again. The Queen of Gqom and head honcho of West Ink, are they okay - we give our views on that and a host of other topics on another fire episode of your favorite podcast.

The Queen of Gqom and head honcho of West Ink, are they okay - we give our views on that and a host of other topics on another fire episode of your favorite podcast.

item.content:encoded: Motshidisi Mohono is an award winning Sport Broadcaster – currently plying her trade at SuperSport International and Vision View Sports Radio. She was recently named Journalist of the Year at the 2018 SA Sport Awards – the first woman in the history of the awards to receive the coveted nod. Her stellar work, that garnered the win, included being part of SuperSport’s production team for the England tour to South Africa; anchoring Super Rugby games in studio and travelling to New Zealand to cover the tournament’s final.

item.content:encoded:
Our first Interview of 2020 features the beautiful and talented Candice Modiselle



Candice Modiselle is a South African actress and presenter best known for her role as Lerato on the SABC1 soap opera Generations: The Legacy. She was previously known as a presenter on the kids show YOTV Live, on SABC1.The sister of entertainers Bontle Modiselle and Refilwe Modiselle, Candice studied Drama as a high school subject from Grade 10 to Matric at McAuley House Convent in Parktown, Johannesburg.She was one of six finalists in the ACT DALRO performance scholarship competition 2012 and she graduated from the University of Witwatersrand in 2017 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Dramatic Arts (Honours).Candice landed a presenting gig on YOTV Live in June 2016, spending two years on the show before leaving in June 2018.During her time on YOTV she landed the recurring role of Lerato on the SABC1 soapie Generations: The Legacy, making her first appearance on 12 January, 2017.She was also a guest presenter on the SABC1 music shows Live AMP and Selimathunzi in 2018.Candice was one of four celebrities who were featured on the first episode of the fifth season of the BBC Brit reality series Come Dine With Me South Africa, a celebrity special which aired on 11 March, 2019.In 2019 she landed her first starring role in television in the 1Magic / Mzansi Magic drama series Impilo (The Scam)
